name: get_technical_indicator_of_ticker
description: Technical indicator APIs for a given equity or currency exchange pair, derived from the underlying time series based stock API and forex data. All indicators are calculated from adjusted time series data to eliminate artificial price/volume perturbations from historical split and dividend events.

indicator_symbol.description: The symbol of the technical indicator you inquire.

interval.description: Time interval between two consecutive data points in the time series. The following values are supported: hourly, daily, weekly, monthly.

symbol.description: The name of the ticker of your choice. For example: symbol=IBM.

series_type.description: The desired price type in the time series. Four types are supported: close, open, high, low.

apikey.description: API-KEY required to access this information.

name: get_all_technical_indicators_available
description: Get all technical indicators this script is available to.

name: get_technical_indicator_description
description: Get description of a technical indicator by an indicator symbol.

indicator_symbol.description: The symbol of the technical indicator you inquire.

name: ask_to_user
description: You can ask user for guidance when you think you need more information to handle the task, but you should use this tool as less as you can.

question.description: The question you want to ask to user.

name: finish
description: Finish the task and give your answer.
